SP  - 1179
EP  - 1200
VL  - 57
IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12194
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - ??Buy local? arrangements encourage members of a community or group to patronize one another instead of the external economy. They range from formal mechanisms such as local currencies to informal ?I'll buy from you if you buy from me? arrangements and are often championed on social or environmental grounds. We show that in a monopolistically competitive economy, buy local arrangements can have salutary effects even for selfish agents immune to social or environmental considerations. Buy local arrangements effectively allow firms to exploit the equilibrium price?cost gap to profitably expand their sales at the going price.
ER  - 

