IS  - 4
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0020-6598
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/iere.12199
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - To evaluate fiscal policy reforms for Euro-area countries, this article develops and calibrates a small open economy model. Debt reduction reforms require higher tax rates in the short term in exchange for lower rates in the long term as the debt-servicing burden falls. Using the capital income tax to implement such a policy leads to welfare gains; the consumption tax, a very small welfare gain; and the labor income tax, a welfare loss. Holding fixed the long-run debt?output ratio, offsetting a lower capital income tax with either a higher labor income or consumption tax generally yields welfare gains.
ER  - 

